IndexedDenseDoubleMatrix2D

public IndexedDenseDoubleMatrix2D(net.casper.data.model.CDataRowSet cdrs)
                           throws net.casper.data.model.CDataGridException
Construct an instance from a CDataRowSet. Generates an index array of the primary key columns in the dataset, and stores these internally in the object instance. The matrix is then set up with all other columns, which must contain doubles.

Parameters:
cdrs - a casper CDataRowSet
Throws:
net.casper.data.model.CDataGridException - if problem reading dataset
IllegalArgumentException - if a non double value is encountered or some other problem with the CDataRowSet

indexLookupRow

public int indexLookupRow(Object[] key)
Does a lookup in the index for the supplied key and returns the corresponding matrix row number. The caller requires knowledge of the dataset primary key types, eg: if the type of the primary key is Double[] then passing in an Object[] with Integer[] values will throw an exception.

Parameters:
key - a primary key value
Returns:
row number, or exception thrown if key is not found
